W9s5ON5799wVCvloMin3f7HySx2zlHQXtOfsJiQHggeTA==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating library setup needs**\\n\\nI’m contemplating whether the library setup requires more than just the usual test scaffold for meaningful coverage. If existing tests suggest extra setup is needed, I'll note dependency for the future without modifying the repository details. I might formulate a JSON single object for this. About agent guidance: it should indicate avoiding Docker and favor in-memory construction and mock servlet requests instead of needing a live server. However, I worry if mentioning deterministic dependencies could violate guidelines against restating entries.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering risks with WebDAV and testing**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the risks involved: having a live WebDAV server seems excessive, and external integration tests may lead to flaky I/O. Plus, native-image might still face issues due to version behavior in AbstractLocatorFactory rather than the setup itself. I believe my Local Gradle and Native Image verification should be reliable. However, the existing failures in locator tests indicate there might be version-specific assertions or behavior at play, which is something to consider further.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Meaningful coverage of jackrabbit-webdav includes servlet-facing WebDAV server/request/response APIs, but the artifact declares servlet-api as a provided dependency, so the normal test scaffold should add it explicitly.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"javax.servlet:servlet-api:2.4\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"jackrabbit-webdav 2.0-beta4 declares javax.servlet:servlet-api as provided, while core classes such as AbstractWebdavServlet, DavServletRequest/Response, InputContextImpl, OutputContextImpl, and header helpers reference javax.servlet types; existing tests for 1.5.0 already add this dependency for the same reason.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker service or environment variable appears necessary. Prefer in-memory API coverage: construct WebDAV method/info/report/property objects directly, and use small HttpServletRequest/HttpServletResponse test doubles for servlet-facing classes instead of starting a WebDAV server.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The project README says this artifact is a library for building WebDAV servers/clients, not a full deployable WebDAV server; adding a container or external repository would likely be unnecessary and flaky.\",\n    \"The reported native-image failures in AbstractLocatorFactory tests look like version-specific behavioral/assertion issues rather than missing external setup.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0eb11ca61208bf6f016a42a3a7c11c81938bcec8d4d1936050\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3127, "output": 831, "cacheRead": 28160, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32118, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782752156918, "responseId": "resp_0eb11ca61208bf6f016a42a39d78e48193846f1f6bd556be3e"}}
